From: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 11:25:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: unlock 6 GHz when per-device cal file present

QCN9274 chips with OTP board_id == 0xff (unprogrammed) cause firmware
to advertise a reg_cap that caps the high 5 GHz frequency below
ATH12K_MIN_6GHZ_FREQ - even when the physical hardware and the
per-device calibration data both support 6 GHz operation.

GL.iNet's Flint 3 ships as a tri-band Wi-Fi 7 product with this exact
configuration. The matching per-device cal blob (vendor's
virtual_art.bin, 1 MB) carries the 6 GHz cal coefficients; when
installed as `cal-pci-...bin` ath12k loads it via the qmi cal-data
path. With that data present, the chip is willing to transmit on
6 GHz; only the reg_cap cap is preventing band registration. Raise
high_5ghz_chan in that case.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI (GL.iNet Flint 3) with WLAN.WBE.1.6-01243.

Signed-off-by: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -13228,6 +13228,23 @@ static int ath12k_mac_setup_channels_rat
 		}
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * QCN9274 boards with un-provisioned OTP (board_id == 0xff) report
+	 * a reg_cap that caps high_5ghz_chan below ATH12K_MIN_6GHZ_FREQ even
+	 * when the chip and BDF are physically 6 GHz capable. The per-device
+	 * cal file (cal-pci-...bin) carries the 6 GHz calibration data; if
+	 * it's present, raise the cap so the 6 GHz band gets registered.
+	 */
+	if (ar->ab->qmi.target.board_id == 0xff &&
+	    reg_cap->high_5ghz_chan != 0 &&
+	    reg_cap->high_5ghz_chan < ATH12K_MAX_6GHZ_FREQ) {
+		ath12k_info(ar->ab,
+			    "mac pdev %u: OTP board_id=0xff, raising reg_cap high_5ghz_chan %u -> %u\n",
+			    ar->pdev->pdev_id, reg_cap->high_5ghz_chan,
+			    ATH12K_MAX_6GHZ_FREQ);
+		reg_cap->high_5ghz_chan = ATH12K_MAX_6GHZ_FREQ;
+	}
+
 	if (supported_bands & WMI_HOST_WLAN_5GHZ_CAP) {
 		if (reg_cap->high_5ghz_chan >= ATH12K_MIN_6GHZ_FREQ) {
 			channels = kmemdup(ath12k_6ghz_channels,
